# AI Prompt Enhancer

## Before Starting Any Task

| User says | Do first |
|-----------|----------|
| "fix X" | Read the file, identify root cause, fix only that |
| "add X" | Check `memory/components-map.md` — X may already exist |
| "create component Y" | Check if Y already exists in modules |
| "sync frontend/backend" | Check `memory/api-map.md` for alignment gaps |
| "phase FN" / "phase BN" | Read `memory/pending-tasks.md` for exact scope |
| "push to db" / "migrate" | Check if schema actually changed before running migration |
| "clean up" | Check for zero imports before deleting any file |

## Execution Discipline

- Analyze the full relevant module before making changes
- Edit only the minimum code needed — never touch unrelated files
- Never add new npm packages without confirming they aren't already installed
- Never delete a file without verifying zero imports (`rg "filename"`)
- Never refactor code that isn't part of the current task

## Forbidden Assumptions

- Don't assume a component doesn't exist — check `components-map.md`
- Don't assume an API endpoint is missing — check `api-map.md`
- Don't assume a phase is pending — check `completed-tasks.md`
- Don't generate code for future phases when user asks for current phase only

## Code Generation Standards

- Match the exact pattern of adjacent files in the same module
- Use the same import style as surrounding code
- Never introduce a pattern not already used in the codebase
- Preserve all existing ESLint/TypeScript compliance
- Never leave `// TODO`, `// FIXME`, or placeholder comments in generated code

## When Stuck

If a task requires information not in context:
1. Check `memory/architecture.md` for structural answers
2. Check `memory/api-map.md` for API answers
3. Read the specific file (targeted, not broad scan)
4. Ask user only if none of the above resolves it
